\begin{aligned}
& \underbrace{\left(\begin{array}{c}
Y_{t} \\
z_{t}
\end{array}\right)}_{W_{t}}=\underbrace{\left(\begin{array}{c}
\Pi \\
0_{r \times n p}
\end{array}\right)}_{\Gamma} X_{t}+\underbrace{\left(\begin{array}{c}
u_{t} \\
z_{t}
\end{array}\right)}_{\eta_{t}} \\
& \underbrace{\left(\begin{array}{c}
u_{t} \\
z_{t}
\end{array}\right)}_{\eta_{t}}=\underbrace{\left(\begin{array}{cc}
H & \\
R_{z} & \Omega_{t r}
\end{array}\right)}_{\xi_{t}} \underbrace{\left(\begin{array}{c}
\varepsilon_{t} \\
\zeta_{t}
\end{array}\right)}_{\xi_{t}}=\left(\begin{array}{ccc}
H_{\bullet 1} & H_{\bullet 2} & \\
\Phi & \Upsilon & \Omega_{t r}
\end{array}\right) \underbrace{\left(\begin{array}{c}
\varepsilon_{1, t} \\
\varepsilon_{2, t} \\
\zeta_{t}
\end{array}\right)}_{\xi_{t}}
\end{aligned}
$$

where $R_{z}$ contains the relevance parameters and possibly the contamination parameters (when $\Upsilon \neq 0_{r \times(n-k)}$ ), and $\xi_{t}$ stacks the structural shocks $\varepsilon_{t}$ and the normalized measurement errors $\zeta_{t}$, such that $\mathbb{E}\left(\xi_{t} \xi_{t}^{\prime}\right)=I_{n+r}$; see, e.g., Angelini and Fanelli (2019), Arias et al. (2021) and Giacomini et al. (2022) for similar representations. ${ }^{4}$ The top-right empty block within

